It was pretty hot inside therefore I think they really should have put on their AC. However the work they do doesn’t last. The first time I visited for a manicure and pedicure they did not apply any top coat. The following week I went back and specifically asked that they apply a top coat, which they did. However, even after waiting 40 mins for my polish to fully dry it remained tacky and was damaged before I even left the salon. They need to invest in some Seche Vite or similar to fix their work.

There is a persisting problem of the credit card machine not working - no information given often of that so you land up and have to walk to the nearest atm to get the payable amount, which is very irritating!
Of late, I have noticed that some polishes have dried up but they keep using them - it just takes so much time to dry even under the fan drier.

The shop was nicely decorated and very clean. The employees are nice and well mannered. Services were timely and they did a good job on a set of gel nails( Not extensions).
There are signs all over that says 500 for full set.
Music would be nice, it’s too quiet inside.
They did a very nice job on my gel nail set.

Cons:
I didn’t get a full set but was charged same price. I believe they overcharged me.
They don’t offer full service pedicures, everywhere i have been before atleast rinses your feet before doing nails.

I found it a bit uncomfortable as they have no stools to prop your feet up while doing your toe nails. I didn’t like having to hold one foot up at a time under a table. I felt twisted as they were doing my hand at the same time above the table so i had to stretch and sit on the edge of my chair so that the person doing my toenails could reach from under the table while balancing to keep my foot accessible to them in their lap.
They acted as if it was my problem that i got tired from stress of holding my foot up. They need to be better organized.
Also they need to keep the chit chat amongst themselves to a minimum when they are working with a client. We don’t need to feel like they don’t care about what they are doing, when they are doing it.
👎🏻 overall review. I will never be coming back here.

This could be remedied in one of 3 ways:
Do hands and feet separately
Use a stool for support instead of lap or
Use a salon chair with side desk so both hands and feet are assessable at same time.","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMZDuCnEjY4YYxny5OzAe40xqR59oHWiSxTZ37b=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"10 months ago"}]
